		\begin{flushleft}
			
			\textbf{3.5 Environments} \bigskip			

			In \LaTeX{} environments are macros that can be used to apply specific formats to a section of the document, 
			for example to align or centre text, to generate a table or to create lists. 
			To initiate an environment the \textit{\textbackslash begin\{\}} command is used, 
			which must be closed with the \textit{\textbackslash end\{\}} command. 
			Options must be placed after the environment name to avoid any collisions.
			Finally, environments can in themselves contain (further) environments, which, however, 
			must be closed before the overarching environment ends: 

		\end{flushleft}
		
