			\textbf{4. Packages} \bigskip
			
			Packages are macros that supplement the base functionality of \LaTeX{} by adding on
			new functions or features. 
			To use packages they first need to be loaded in, which can be done by including them in the 
			preamble via the \textit{\textbackslash usepackage\{\}} directive. 
			Once a package is loaded in, any function from that package may be called upon 
			(e.g. the \textit{\textbackslash enquote\{\}} function from the \foreignlanguage{english}{\enquote*{csquotes}} package).
			While the order in which packages are listed in the preamble is generally free, it may matter depending on
